# Guardrails (grep-first)

Before finishing any PR that touches user-facing strings or data paths:

1. No `BUY`/`SELL`/"guaranteed"/"risk-free" in user-facing output (whitelist enforcement code in `benchmark.py` / tests that assert the ban).
2. Action fields only: WATCH | HOLD | ACCUMULATE | REDUCE | AVOID | INSUFFICIENT_DATA.
3. Never fabricate missing prices/fundamentals — surface INSUFFICIENT_DATA / MISSING.
4. Confidence capped by QualityStatus precedence in `quality.py`.
5. No secrets in source/fixtures; `.env` gitignored.
6. No LLM calls in ingestion path modules.
7. No broker SDKs; no options/futures/crypto/margin/intraday paths this phase.

Use the `guardrail-auditor` agent (or `.claude/skills/guardrail-check`) before merge.
